{{Politics of Costa Rica}}
[[File:Partidopala.jpg|thumb|Flag of the Agrarian Labour Action Party|345px]]


The '''Agricultural Labour Action Party''' ({{lang-es|Partido Acción Laborista Agrícola}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Costa Rica]]. 

The party was founded after the end of the [[Agrarian Politics Union Party]]. The first general elections contested by the party were in [[Costa Rican general election, 1990|1990]], in which it received only 0.4% of the vote, and failed to win a seat. In [[Costa Rican general election, 1994|1994]] its vote share dropped to 0.3%, again failing to win a seat. In [[Costa Rican general election, 1998|1998]] its electoral performance improved, as it received 1.2% of the national vote and winning its first seat. However, in [[Costa Rican general election, 2002|2002]] its vote share dropped to 0.7% and it lost its parliamentary representation.<ref name=DN>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p175 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref>

