A '''benefactor''' ({{Etymology|la|bene|good||factor|maker}}) is a person who gives some form of help to benefit a person, group or organization (the [[beneficiary]]), often gifting a monetary contribution in the form of an endowment to help a cause. Benefactors are humanitarian leaders and charitable patrons providing assistance in many forms, such as an [[alumnus]] from a university giving back to a college or an individual providing assistance to others.

