'''Colour retention agents''' are [[food additives]] that are added to food to prevent the colour from changing. Many of them work by absorbing or binding to oxygen before it can damage food ([[antioxidants]]). For example, [[ascorbic acid]] ([[vitamin]] C) is often added to brightly coloured fruits such as [[peach]]es during [[canning]].{{Citation needed|date=May 2009}}
