{{Orphan|date=April 2015}} '''Jared Israel''' (born 1944) is an American writer, [[activist]] and [[conspiracy theory|conspiracy theorist]]<ref name="Knight">Peter Knight “[https://www.jstor.org/stable/27669225 Outrageous Conspiracy Theories: Popular and Official Responses to 9/11 in Germany and the United States]” New German Critique, No. 103, Dark Powers: Conspiracies and Conspiracy Theory in History and Literature (Winter, 2008), pp. 165-193 Published by: Duke University Press Stable URL: https://www.jstor.org/stable/27669225 Accessed: 30-01-2018 16:25 UTC</ref> who edits the website ''The Emperor’s New Clothes'', and has been published in ''[[Arutz Sheva]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jared Israel|url=http://www.israelnationalnews.com/Articles/Author.aspx/166|title=Articles by Jared Israel|accessdate=February 9, 2009|publisher=[[Arutz Sheva]]}}</ref> He graduated from [[Harvard University]] where he was involved in student protests,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1969/05/02/archives/169-fined-in-harvard-sitin-2-cleared-at-cambridge-judge-finds-169.html|title=169 Fined in Harvard Sit-In; 2 Cleared at Cambridge|accessdate=February 9, 2009|author=Robert M. Smith|date=May 2, 1969|publisher=''[[The New York Times]]''}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1967/05/09/archives/70-youths-ejected-in-protest-on-draft-at-house-building.html|title=70 Youths Ejected In Protest on Draft At House Building|accessdate=February 9, 2009|date=May 9, 1967|publisher=''[[The New York Times]]''}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-8115756.html|title=Harvard, Ex-Radicals Remember Many Talk of Feelings 20 Years After Protest|accessdate=February 9, 2009|author=Alexander Reid|date=April 9, 1989|publisher=''[[The Boston Globe]]''}}</ref> and also attended [[Columbia University]]. At Harvard he was a co-chairman of [[Students for a Democratic Society (SDS)]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecrimson.com/article/1967/10/28/mallinckrodt-pbfbred-leavitts-a-nice-guy/?print=1|title=Mallinckrodt -- At one time the leaders thought they had enough power to force Harvard on recruiting policies|accessdate=December 30, 2010|author=W. Bruce Springer|date=October 28, 1967|publisher=[[The Harvard Crimson]]}}</ref> and, in April 1969, a leader of the University Hall building takeover that was broken up by hundreds of outside police, in response to which Harvard students went on strike, closing Harvard for the only time in its history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/586091842.html?dids=586091842:586091842&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Sep+22%2C+1969&author=&pub=Chicago+Tribune&desc=HARVARD+IS+WARNED&pqatl=google|title=Harvard is Warned|accessdate=December 30, 2010|date=September 22, 1969|publisher=''[[Chicago Tribune]]''}}</ref>
Israel served as one of the co-chairmen of the International Committee to Defend [[Slobodan Milošević]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2002/aug/06/world/fg-milo6|title=Milosevic’s Defiance Is Taking Its Toll on Him–and His Trial|accessdate=February 9, 2009|author=Carol J. Williams|date=August 6, 2002|publisher=''[[Los Angeles Times]]''}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/low/europe/2220997.stm|title=Analysis: Milosevic and the missing link|accessdate=February 9, 2009|author=Bill Hayton |date=28 August 2002|publisher=[[BBC News]]}}</ref> He has denied events leading to [[Srebrenica massacre|Srebrenica genocide]]and its consequences,<ref name="helsinki.org.rs-Denial.doc">{{cite web |title=CONFRONTING SREBRENICA GENOCIDE DENIAL |url=https://www.helsinki.org.rs/doc/Confronting%20Srebrenica%20Genocide%20Denial.doc |website=helsinki.org.rs |accessdate=14 October 2018 |format=ms word .doc |date=23 June 2009}}</ref><ref name="helsinki.org.rs-tjsrebrenica">{{cite web |title=Srebrenica ::: Helsinki Committee for Human Rights in Serbia |url=https://www.helsinki.org.rs/tjsrebrenica.html |website=www.helsinki.org.rs |accessdate=14 October 2018}}</ref> and condemned [[2008 Kosovo declaration of independence|Kosovo's independence]] as being illegal and in fact having been orchestrated by the [[United States]], [[Germany]] and the [[Holy See|Vatican]].
Jared Israel has written a great deal analyzing and challenging the mainstream account of what happened during the [[September 11 attacks]] and suggesting it was an "inside job".<ref name="Knight"/>
