{{MOS|date=March 2016}} [[File:Kunglig Hovleverantör.jpeg|thumb|Purveyors to the Court of Sweden are entitled to display the [[Coat of Arms of Sweden|royal coat of arms]] with the motto ''Kunglig hovleverantör'' underneath.]] '''Royal warrants of appointment''' in [[Sweden]] are granted to the purveyor ({{lang-sv|Kunglig hovleverantör}}) by the [[King of Sweden|king]] or the [[Queen of Sweden|queen]]. To qualify for a warrant, the order must come from the royal court and the company must deliver its goods or services to the court. A royal warrant is personal and usually awarded to the managing director of the company rather than the company itself. All goods and services are paid for by the court.<ref> {{cite web |url = http://www.hovlev.se/faq_e.html |title = Royal Warrant Holders in Sweden - FAQ |publisher = www.hovlev.se |accessdate = 2008-06-02 |last = |first = |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20051210111403/http://www.hovlev.se/faq_e.html |archivedate = 2005-12-10 |df = }} </ref>
